Data Preproccessing¶

In [3]:
def song_year(song_title):
	x=str(df[df['song_title']==song_title]['pub_year'].unique())
	x=x.split('-')[0]
	return int(x[1:-1])

def genre(song_title):
	x=str(df[df['song_title']==song_title]['genre'].unique())
	return x[2:-2]
In [4]:
u=df[['song_title','listen_count','is_favorite','is_added_to_playlist']]
u=u.groupby('song_title').sum()
x=pd.DataFrame(u.index)
x.reset_index()
y=x['song_title'].apply(song_year)
g=x['song_title'].apply(genre)
u['genre']=[g[i] for i in range(0,len(g))]
u['pub_year']=[y[i] for i in range(0,len(y))]
u

Data Analysis¶

In [9]:
# Using the elbow method to find the optimal number of clusters
wcss = []
for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = i, init = 'k-means++', random_state = 0)
    kmeans.fit(SX)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
plt.plot(range(1, 11), wcss)
plt.title('The Elbow Method')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
plt.ylabel('WCSS')
plt.show()
